# Zsh Advanced Tips
# Format: alias|old_command_pattern|description|example

# Shell shortcuts
c|clear|Clear terminal screen|c
reload|source ~/.zshrc|Reload shell configuration|reload
reload|. ~/.zshrc|Reload shell configuration|reload
zshrc|$EDITOR ~/.zshrc|Edit zsh configuration|zshrc
aliases|$EDITOR ~/.aliases|Edit aliases file|aliases
brewup|brew update|Update Homebrew and all packages|brewup

# Editor shortcuts (all open nvim)
vi|vi |Neovim (aliased from vi)|vi file.txt
vim|vim |Neovim (aliased from vim)|vim file.txt
nvim|nano |Neovim (aliased from nano)|nvim file.txt

# Language shortcuts
py|python3|Python 3 shortcut|py script.py

# Archive shortcuts
untar|tar -xvf|Extract tar archive|untar archive.tar.gz

Ctrl-x Ctrl-e|vim|Edit current command in your editor|Type command, then Ctrl-x Ctrl-e
Ctrl-_|undo|Undo last edit in command line|After Ctrl-w, press Ctrl-_
!!|sudo|Repeat last command (use with sudo)|sudo !!
magic-space|history|Expand !! before running with spacebar|sudo !! then space
zmv|mv *.foo|Batch rename files with patterns|zmv '(*).log' '$1.txt'
hash -d|cd /long/path|Create named directory bookmarks|hash -d YT=/path/to/youtube
alias -s|./file.go|Open files by extension automatically|alias -s go=nvim
alias -g|2>/dev/null|Global aliases expand anywhere|alias -g NE='2>/dev/null'
Ctrl-x l|clear|Clear screen but keep current command|Ctrl-x then l
bindkey -s|boilerplate|Create hotkeys that insert text|bindkey -s '^g' 'git status\n'
